{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "30", "m": "05", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "05", "M": "40", "S": "15"}}, "news": [{"title": "NMMC has authority to collect property tax in Thane-Belapur industrial belt: SC", "para": "The Supreme Court has ruled that the Navi Mumbai Municipal Corporation can collect property tax from industries in the Thane Trans Creek-MIDC area. This decision settles a long-standing dispute. The court clarified the difference between taxes and fees, empowering NMMC to levy taxes. This will boost city development with over Rs 800 crore in pending dues.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/supreme-court-upholds-nmmcs-authority-to-collect-property-tax-in-thane-belapur-industrial-corridor/131403558?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-833578/131403558.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Telangana: Raidurg land fetches \u20b95,000 crore in eight months", "para": "Raidurg, Hyderabad's Knowledge City, has generated over Rs 5,000 crore for Telangana in just eight months. High-value land auctions have made this two-square-kilometre area the state's most valuable real estate hotspot. IT majors and corporate giants are anchoring projects here. Kokapet is the second major hotspot. Raidurg's land valuations are extraordinary.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/record-breaking-land-auctions-telanganas-raidurg-fetches-5000-crore-in-eight-months/131403519?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-80686/131403519.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "CREDAI Visakhapatnam seeks simplified registration for large housing projects under CARD 2.0", "para": "CREDAI Visakhapatnam has urged the stamps and registration department to implement a project ID-based framework under CARD 2.0. This initiative aims to streamline registration for large residential projects by reducing repetitive data entry and verification processes. The proposed system would enhance efficiency and speed up registrations for developers and applicants.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/credai-visakhapatnam-advocates-project-id-system-to-simplify-housing-registration-process/131403354?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-216313/131403354.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}]}